<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="229" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,327,679]" pageId="14" pageNumber="229">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,435,462]" pageId="14" pageNumber="229">Comments</emphasis>
. This is the 
<typeStatus box="[462,510,437,463]" pageId="14" pageNumber="229">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Steffan, 1969" authorityName="Steffan" authorityYear="1969" box="[745,1031,436,462]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Lobosciara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="229" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[745,873,436,462]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="229">Lobosciara</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Steffan, W. A." box="[879,1031,436,462]" pageId="14" pageNumber="229" pagination="669 - 732" refId="ref10929" refString="Steffan, W. A. (1969) Insects of Micronesia. Diptera: Sciaridae. Insects of Micronesia, 12 (7), 669 - 732." type="journal article" year="1969">Steffan, 1969</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Sasakawa" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[1041,1303,436,462]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Lobosciara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="229" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinipennis">
<emphasis box="[1041,1303,436,462]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="229">Lobosciara spinipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(along with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Steffan" authorityYear="1973" box="[151,263,472,498]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="229" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bishopi">
<emphasis box="[151,263,472,498]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="229">B. bishopi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), are common on the islands of 
<collectingCountry box="[619,749,472,498]" name="Micronesia" pageId="14" pageNumber="229">Micronesia</collectingCountry>
. They comprised 90% of the specimens that Steffan identified during his 
<collectingCountry box="[271,397,508,534]" name="Micronesia" pageId="14" pageNumber="229">Micronesia</collectingCountry>
study (
<bibRefCitation author="Steffan, W. A." box="[479,628,508,535]" pageId="14" pageNumber="229" pagination="669 - 732" refId="ref10929" refString="Steffan, W. A. (1969) Insects of Micronesia. Diptera: Sciaridae. Insects of Micronesia, 12 (7), 669 - 732." type="journal article" year="1969">Steffan 1969</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,327,679]" pageId="14" pageNumber="229">
It is interesting to note that in late 1992, there was an outbreak of sciarids following severe defoliation of trees on 
<collectingCountry box="[186,254,580,606]" name="Guam" pageId="14" pageNumber="229">Guam</collectingCountry>
caused by typhoon Gay, with windrows of the dead flies (presumed to be 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Sasakawa" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[1087,1244,581,606]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Lobosciara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="229" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinipennis">
<emphasis box="[1087,1244,581,606]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="229">L. spinipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) found along the shoreline and around buildings for weeks after the storm (
<bibRefCitation author="Kerr, A. M." box="[799,920,616,642]" pageId="14" pageNumber="229" pagination="895 - 901" refId="ref9313" refString="Kerr, A. M. (2000) Defoliation of an island (Guam, Mariana Archipelago, Western Pacific Ocean) following a saltspray-laden &quot; dry &quot; typhoon. Journal of Tropical Ecology, 16, 895 - 901. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0266467400001796" type="journal article" year="2000">Kerr 2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
